<p dir=3D"auto" class=3D"break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md=
:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Even if your quant=
 forum is quite large (say 50,000=E2=80=93100,000 chunks), it stays comfort=
ably under <strong class=3D"font-semibold">4 GB peak</strong>.
Most modern Windows machines (16 GB or 32 GB RAM) will run this smoothly wi=
th plenty of headroom for other apps.</p>
<h3 dir=3D"auto" class=3D"font-semibold text-xl max-md:font-display max-md:=
text-[19px] max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:tracking-[0px] max-md:mb-3 max-md:=
mt-3">Why It=E2=80=99s So Light (Key Reasons)</h3>
<ul dir=3D"auto" class=3D"marker:text-secondary">
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">No local=
 LLM</strong> =E2=86=92 Gemini runs in the cloud via your proxy. Your PC on=
ly sends tiny text requests.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Embeddin=
gs are tiny</strong> =E2=86=92 The fallback (all-MiniLM-L6-v2) uses only ~1=
00=E2=80=93200 MB when loaded. The preferred proxy embeddings use zero loca=
l RAM.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">Chroma i=
s smart</strong> =E2=86=92 It stores everything on disk (your D: drive) and=
 only loads the index + retrieved chunks into memory during searches. It do=
es <strong class=3D"font-semibold">not</strong> keep the entire forum in RA=
M.</li>
<li class=3D"break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-norma=
l [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal"><strong class=3D"font-semibold">CrewAI i=
s lightweight</strong> in our setup =E2=86=92 Sequential process, no heavy =
